00:33:26.040 --> 00:33:29.220 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we start adding
in-- you get the idea.

00:33:29.220 --> 00:33:30.810 align:middle line:84%
Imagine, the
burgers, the fries--

00:33:30.810 --> 00:33:35.340 align:middle line:84%
the years upon years of neglect,
and cigarettes, and alcohol,

00:33:35.340 --> 00:33:36.720 align:middle line:90%
and all kinds of stuff.

00:33:36.720 --> 00:33:40.980 align:middle line:84%
Now, imagine we now change
that and it becomes very, very

00:33:40.980 --> 00:33:41.880 align:middle line:90%
dirty.

00:33:41.880 --> 00:33:44.370 align:middle line:90%
The fish is a survival machine.

00:33:44.370 --> 00:33:47.790 align:middle line:84%
It is designed to
survive above all else.

00:33:47.790 --> 00:33:49.950 align:middle line:90%
Health comes second.

00:33:49.950 --> 00:33:51.552 align:middle line:90%
Survival is number one.

00:33:51.552 --> 00:33:53.760 align:middle line:84%
So what will happen if it's
swimming around like this

00:33:53.760 --> 00:33:57.030 align:middle line:84%
and it started, for example,
to get a little cough.

00:33:57.030 --> 00:33:58.470 align:middle line:90%
Now, here's the weird thing.

00:33:58.470 --> 00:34:02.222 align:middle line:84%
If it started to cough, it
would go and see a doctor.

00:34:02.222 --> 00:34:03.930 align:middle line:84%
So it goes and sees
a little fish doctor.

00:34:03.930 --> 00:34:07.700 align:middle line:84%
The fish doctor says, you
need some syrup for the cough.

00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:11.219 align:middle line:84%
Now, one look at the
cause of the problem,

00:34:11.219 --> 00:34:13.110 align:middle line:90%
just looking at the symptom.

00:34:13.110 --> 00:34:15.290 align:middle line:84%
Then, after a little while,
you put some syrup in,

00:34:15.290 --> 00:34:16.350 align:middle line:90%
it stops coughing.

00:34:16.350 --> 00:34:17.820 align:middle line:90%
The fish is happy again.

00:34:17.820 --> 00:34:19.903 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't understand there
is any problem at all.

00:34:19.903 --> 00:34:22.050 align:middle line:84%
It starts swimming around
in all the crap again.

00:34:22.050 --> 00:34:24.217 align:middle line:84%
And then what happens is,
the little fin at the back

00:34:24.217 --> 00:34:25.710 align:middle line:90%
now can't move properly.

00:34:25.710 --> 00:34:27.918 align:middle line:84%
It's got kind of
arthritis at the back.

00:34:27.918 --> 00:34:29.460 align:middle line:84%
So he goes along to
his doctor again.

00:34:29.460 --> 00:34:32.909 align:middle line:84%
He says, hey, doctor,
look, I can't move my fin.

00:34:32.909 --> 00:34:35.580 align:middle line:84%
He says, that's OK,
here's some cortisone.

00:34:35.580 --> 00:34:38.339 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to inject your
fin, and now it can move again.

00:34:38.339 --> 00:34:39.139 align:middle line:90%
Oh, thank you.

00:34:39.139 --> 00:34:41.040 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much, doctor.

00:34:41.040 --> 00:34:42.929 align:middle line:84%
What happens if it
starts to bloat up?

00:34:42.929 --> 00:34:46.350 align:middle line:84%
What happens if it starts to
get psoriasis on the skin?

00:34:46.350 --> 00:34:48.389 align:middle line:84%
Look, the point I'm
making is this--

00:34:48.389 --> 00:34:51.449 align:middle line:84%
this analogy usually
takes a lot longer.

00:34:51.449 --> 00:34:52.800 align:middle line:90%
The point is this though--

00:34:52.800 --> 00:34:56.730 align:middle line:84%
if it's swimming around
in a polluted environment,

00:34:56.730 --> 00:35:01.260 align:middle line:84%
then the body will use its
filtration system to survive.

00:35:01.260 --> 00:35:03.810 align:middle line:84%
But at what cost to
his daily health?

00:35:03.810 --> 00:35:07.070 align:middle line:84%
But then, we're not
looking at the symptom.

00:35:07.070 --> 00:35:09.270 align:middle line:84%
So we're not looking at
the cause of the problem.

00:35:09.270 --> 00:35:11.270 align:middle line:84%
What we're doing is trying
to treat the symptom.

00:35:11.270 --> 00:35:13.380 align:middle line:84%
So what happens is, if
it gets really bad, then

00:35:13.380 --> 00:35:14.650 align:middle line:90%
we go to the doctor.

00:35:14.650 --> 00:35:16.380 align:middle line:84%
The doctor will get
some tablets and then

00:35:16.380 --> 00:35:19.200 align:middle line:84%
the tablets will then go
into the bowl as well.

00:35:19.200 --> 00:35:23.070 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that all
medical drugs are toxic.

00:35:23.070 --> 00:35:24.570 align:middle line:84%
Of course, they
are, to some degree.

00:35:24.570 --> 00:35:26.410 align:middle line:84%
They're all poisons
to some degree.

00:35:26.410 --> 00:35:28.200 align:middle line:84%
So you add to the
whole environment--

00:35:28.200 --> 00:35:31.560 align:middle line:84%
Look, I've done talks with
the little goldfish in schools

00:35:31.560 --> 00:35:33.930 align:middle line:90%
with children as young as six.

00:35:33.930 --> 00:35:37.020 align:middle line:84%
And I say, if you want to help
this fish out, to get better,

00:35:37.020 --> 00:35:38.370 align:middle line:90%
what would you do?

00:35:38.370 --> 00:35:42.780 align:middle line:84%
And they all shout in
unison, clean the water!

00:35:42.780 --> 00:35:45.360 align:middle line:90%
It seems so blatantly obvious.

00:35:45.360 --> 00:35:48.940 align:middle line:90%


00:35:48.940 --> 00:35:49.740 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:35:49.740 --> 00:35:51.930 align:middle line:84%
It's impossible to slow
down the aging process.

00:35:51.930 --> 00:35:53.070 align:middle line:90%
It's impossible.

00:35:53.070 --> 00:35:55.200 align:middle line:84%
The amount of people trying to
do that with different creams,

00:35:55.200 --> 00:35:56.575 align:middle line:84%
and sauces, and
everything else--

00:35:56.575 --> 00:35:57.930 align:middle line:90%
even with natural foods.

00:35:57.930 --> 00:36:00.930 align:middle line:84%
They make claims to say,
this will help slow down

00:36:00.930 --> 00:36:01.950 align:middle line:90%
the aging process.

00:36:01.950 --> 00:36:04.290 align:middle line:84%
I have never nor
will I ever say that

00:36:04.290 --> 00:36:06.930 align:middle line:84%
any particular organic,
rich juice will ever

00:36:06.930 --> 00:36:08.370 align:middle line:90%
slow down the aging process.

00:36:08.370 --> 00:36:09.240 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:36:09.240 --> 00:36:11.890 align:middle line:84%
Because all you can do is do a
million things to speed it up.

00:36:11.890 --> 00:36:14.008 align:middle line:84%
You can't do anything
to slow it down.

00:36:14.008 --> 00:36:16.050 align:middle line:84%
And that's why people are
trying to slow it down.

00:36:16.050 --> 00:36:18.008 align:middle line:84%
Because they do too many
things to speed it up.

00:36:18.008 --> 00:36:20.730 align:middle line:84%
You drink caffeine, you
have white, refined sugar,

00:36:20.730 --> 00:36:23.910 align:middle line:84%
you have these full stimulants,
speed up the adrenal glands.

00:36:23.910 --> 00:36:25.020 align:middle line:90%
It's fight or flight.

00:36:25.020 --> 00:36:27.990 align:middle line:84%
Your body thinks it's been
attacked all the time.

00:36:27.990 --> 00:36:30.380 align:middle line:84%
Of course it's going to
speed up the aging process.

00:36:30.380 --> 00:36:32.047 align:middle line:84%
But you can't really
do anything to slow

00:36:32.047 --> 00:36:33.870 align:middle line:84%
it down other
than, have a guess,

00:36:33.870 --> 00:36:36.330 align:middle line:84%
getting rid of the rubbish
and then having what

00:36:36.330 --> 00:36:37.770 align:middle line:90%
the body fundamentally requires.

00:36:37.770 --> 00:36:38.570 align:middle line:90%
It's that easy.

00:36:38.570 --> 00:36:42.570 align:middle line:90%


00:36:42.570 --> 00:36:43.370 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:36:43.370 --> 00:36:45.770 align:middle line:84%
The right mental state
is of vital importance.

00:36:45.770 --> 00:36:49.400 align:middle line:84%
But not positive mental
attitude so much.

00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:51.368 align:middle line:84%
That plays a part,
of course it does.

00:36:51.368 --> 00:36:53.285 align:middle line:84%
You really need to see
the nature of the traps

00:36:53.285 --> 00:36:55.370 align:middle line:84%
for what they are, and
then you're already

00:36:55.370 --> 00:36:56.690 align:middle line:90%
in the right frame of mind.

00:36:56.690 --> 00:36:58.670 align:middle line:90%
Let me give an example.

00:36:58.670 --> 00:37:00.860 align:middle line:84%
To take an old analogy
and go one stage further--

00:37:00.860 --> 00:37:03.230 align:middle line:84%
a fly trying to
get out of a room.

00:37:03.230 --> 00:37:05.480 align:middle line:84%
The window is open,
slightly ajar.

00:37:05.480 --> 00:37:10.220 align:middle line:84%
The stupid fly will go along
and hit the window over and over

00:37:10.220 --> 00:37:11.790 align:middle line:90%
and over and over again.

00:37:11.790 --> 00:37:15.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, anybody watching the fly
would say, you're a stupid fly.

00:37:15.390 --> 00:37:17.340 align:middle line:90%
There's clearly another way.

00:37:17.340 --> 00:37:20.240 align:middle line:84%
However, the fly doesn't
see the other way.

00:37:20.240 --> 00:37:23.660 align:middle line:84%
What, though, if the advice
that you gave the fly was this--

00:37:23.660 --> 00:37:26.250 align:middle line:84%
you're clearly not
positive enough.

00:37:26.250 --> 00:37:28.220 align:middle line:90%
You need to change your mindset.

00:37:28.220 --> 00:37:29.600 align:middle line:90%
I know what I'll do.

00:37:29.600 --> 00:37:33.410 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you get on a plane and
come to a positive thinking fly

00:37:33.410 --> 00:37:34.760 align:middle line:90%
seminar.

00:37:34.760 --> 00:37:37.900 align:middle line:84%
What I want you to do,
Mr. Fly, is walk along

00:37:37.900 --> 00:37:42.340 align:middle line:84%
2000 degrees of burning hot
coals, yelling some mantra.

00:37:42.340 --> 00:37:45.590 align:middle line:84%
And at the end, jump up and down
like you can achieve anything.

00:37:45.590 --> 00:37:47.600 align:middle line:90%
Then, go back to the glass.

00:37:47.600 --> 00:37:49.680 align:middle line:90%
Now the fly is pumped.

00:37:49.680 --> 00:37:50.480 align:middle line:90%
It's ready.

00:37:50.480 --> 00:37:51.350 align:middle line:90%
It's booming.

00:37:51.350 --> 00:37:54.290 align:middle line:84%
It's in a state
like never before.

00:37:54.290 --> 00:37:57.710 align:middle line:84%
It goes up to the window,
hits the glass over and over

00:37:57.710 --> 00:38:02.420 align:middle line:84%
and over again, says
that seminar was rubbish.

00:38:02.420 --> 00:38:05.020 align:middle line:84%
What the seminar didn't
necessarily teach the fly--

00:38:05.020 --> 00:38:06.740 align:middle line:84%
getting to a
positive state, yes.

00:38:06.740 --> 00:38:09.308 align:middle line:84%
But if you're still going
about something the right way,

00:38:09.308 --> 00:38:10.850 align:middle line:84%
you're still not
going to achieve it.

00:38:10.850 --> 00:38:14.950 align:middle line:84%
I can get in the best frame of
mind possible to do the Rubik's

00:38:14.950 --> 00:38:15.940 align:middle line:90%
cube.

00:38:15.940 --> 00:38:17.107 align:middle line:90%
That's not going to help me.

00:38:17.107 --> 00:38:18.190 align:middle line:90%
I need the instructions.

00:38:18.190 --> 00:38:20.973 align:middle line:84%
I may be in this frame where
I think, yes, I can do it.

00:38:20.973 --> 00:38:22.390 align:middle line:84%
But all you need
to do is realize,

00:38:22.390 --> 00:38:23.800 align:middle line:90%
there's always another way.

00:38:23.800 --> 00:38:25.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's the key thing
above anything else.

00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:27.760 align:middle line:90%
There is always another way.

00:38:27.760 --> 00:38:30.730 align:middle line:90%
Think, not hard, but smart.

00:38:30.730 --> 00:38:32.590 align:middle line:84%
There's always an
easy way to do it

00:38:32.590 --> 00:38:34.010 align:middle line:90%
if you know what you're doing.

00:38:34.010 --> 00:38:36.220 align:middle line:84%
So yes, attitude is
very, very important.

00:38:36.220 --> 00:38:37.180 align:middle line:90%
Of course it is.

00:38:37.180 --> 00:38:39.460 align:middle line:84%
But you need the right
attitude to find the right way.

00:38:39.460 --> 00:38:41.260 align:middle line:90%
Not just the positive attitude.

00:38:41.260 --> 00:38:43.690 align:middle line:84%
That alone very rarely,
if ever, succeeds.

00:38:43.690 --> 00:38:48.650 align:middle line:90%


00:38:48.650 --> 00:38:50.160 align:middle line:84%
It seems really odd
in today's world

00:38:50.160 --> 00:38:51.930 align:middle line:84%
that we have more
than ever before,

00:38:51.930 --> 00:38:54.780 align:middle line:84%
and yet we think in
a very lax state.

00:38:54.780 --> 00:38:57.420 align:middle line:84%
What I mean by that is,
there is a world of abundance

00:38:57.420 --> 00:38:59.370 align:middle line:90%
and an attitude of lack.

00:38:59.370 --> 00:39:01.545 align:middle line:84%
And the challenge when you
have an attitude of lack

00:39:01.545 --> 00:39:03.420 align:middle line:84%
is that you never feel
grateful for anything.

00:39:03.420 --> 00:39:06.090 align:middle line:84%
If you don't feel grateful for
anything, you feel unfulfilled.

00:39:06.090 --> 00:39:08.670 align:middle line:84%
And most people are
bitching and moaning

00:39:08.670 --> 00:39:10.933 align:middle line:84%
about having to do
certain things instead

00:39:10.933 --> 00:39:13.350 align:middle line:84%
of getting the opportunity
to-- in fact, even just saying.

00:39:13.350 --> 00:39:15.440 align:middle line:84%
Even when I say it,
I feel different.

00:39:15.440 --> 00:39:19.050 align:middle line:84%
If I say, I have to go and
eat fruits or vegetables today

00:39:19.050 --> 00:39:22.450 align:middle line:84%
as opposed to, I get the
opportunity to go to any shop

00:39:22.450 --> 00:39:23.250 align:middle line:90%
that I want.

00:39:23.250 --> 00:39:24.917 align:middle line:84%
I know I live in a
world where I can get

00:39:24.917 --> 00:39:26.084 align:middle line:90%
the finest produce on earth.

00:39:26.084 --> 00:39:27.625 align:middle line:84%
I'm not even going
to think about it.

00:39:27.625 --> 00:39:29.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to walk 20
miles to go and get it.

00:39:29.610 --> 00:39:30.780 align:middle line:90%
I can just get in my car.

00:39:30.780 --> 00:39:32.110 align:middle line:90%
I can walk and get on my bike.

00:39:32.110 --> 00:39:33.510 align:middle line:90%
I can just go and grab it.

00:39:33.510 --> 00:39:36.480 align:middle line:84%
And I can come home and I've
got the amenities to juice it,

00:39:36.480 --> 00:39:38.790 align:middle line:84%
or to eat it, or to steam
it, or whatever it is.

00:39:38.790 --> 00:39:40.440 align:middle line:84%
But it's there on
a plate for me.

00:39:40.440 --> 00:39:43.360 align:middle line:84%
So I get excited because I
get the opportunity to do it.

00:39:43.360 --> 00:39:44.510 align:middle line:90%
Same with moving my body.

00:39:44.510 --> 00:39:48.730 align:middle line:90%


00:39:48.730 --> 00:39:52.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm very fortunate now
that I live my life by a I

00:39:52.160 --> 00:39:55.220 align:middle line:84%
get-the-opportunity-to
attitude rather than I can't be

00:39:55.220 --> 00:39:56.770 align:middle line:84%
bothered, or I
have to, attitude.

00:39:56.770 --> 00:39:58.520 align:middle line:84%
And the man that really
shaped that for me

00:39:58.520 --> 00:39:59.812 align:middle line:90%
was the late Christopher Reeve.

00:39:59.812 --> 00:40:02.267 align:middle line:84%
This guy was an
incredible mentor

00:40:02.267 --> 00:40:04.100 align:middle line:84%
for many people around
the world, and for me

00:40:04.100 --> 00:40:05.180 align:middle line:90%
in particular.

00:40:05.180 --> 00:40:06.590 align:middle line:84%
I always used to
have an attitude

00:40:06.590 --> 00:40:10.820 align:middle line:84%
with exercising of, oh, well
an hour a day is too much.

00:40:10.820 --> 00:40:13.280 align:middle line:84%
Or I wouldn't exercise
for two or three days.

00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:15.050 align:middle line:84%
Since I watched the
late Christopher

00:40:15.050 --> 00:40:17.720 align:middle line:84%
Reeve say a couple
of sentences, I've

00:40:17.720 --> 00:40:20.900 align:middle line:84%
moved my body genuinely
every single day.

00:40:20.900 --> 00:40:22.490 align:middle line:84%
In fact, there
won't be a day now

00:40:22.490 --> 00:40:23.860 align:middle line:90%
that I will not move my body.

00:40:23.860 --> 00:40:25.980 align:middle line:90%
What he said was this--

00:40:25.980 --> 00:40:27.862 align:middle line:84%
60% of the population
at the time,

00:40:27.862 --> 00:40:29.570 align:middle line:84%
when he was being
interviewed in America,

00:40:29.570 --> 00:40:33.180 align:middle line:84%
had just been classed as
either overweight or obese.

00:40:33.180 --> 00:40:35.990 align:middle line:84%
And he said the one
thing these people can do

00:40:35.990 --> 00:40:40.340 align:middle line:84%
is the one thing that I go
to bed every night and dream

00:40:40.340 --> 00:40:42.300 align:middle line:90%
and pray that I could do.

00:40:42.300 --> 00:40:44.330 align:middle line:90%
And that is to move my body.

00:40:44.330 --> 00:40:47.360 align:middle line:84%
He said, if you've got the
gift of physical movement

00:40:47.360 --> 00:40:51.080 align:middle line:84%
but you don't use it, he
said, that is an insult to me

00:40:51.080 --> 00:40:53.640 align:middle line:84%
and those people like me
who have lost that gift.

00:40:53.640 --> 00:40:54.440 align:middle line:90%
And it is a gift.

00:40:54.440 --> 00:40:56.098 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen
as a gift before.

00:40:56.098 --> 00:40:57.890 align:middle line:84%
Normally, it's only
when you lose something

00:40:57.890 --> 00:40:58.960 align:middle line:90%
that you crave it.

00:40:58.960 --> 00:41:00.960 align:middle line:84%
I thought, I'm not going
to wait till I lose it.

00:41:00.960 --> 00:41:02.768 align:middle line:84%
It's when I wake
up and I can move,

00:41:02.768 --> 00:41:04.310 align:middle line:84%
and I can bounce on
a mini trampoline

00:41:04.310 --> 00:41:08.320 align:middle line:84%
or I can play a game of tennis,
I'm so grateful, genuinely.

00:41:08.320 --> 00:41:12.390 align:middle line:90%


00:41:12.390 --> 00:41:13.420 align:middle line:90%
Is TV making us fatter?

00:41:13.420 --> 00:41:14.220 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:41:14.220 --> 00:41:15.250 align:middle line:90%
There's no question.

00:41:15.250 --> 00:41:16.050 align:middle line:90%
Of course it is.

00:41:16.050 --> 00:41:20.800 align:middle line:84%
Listen, I've got a theory on
the TV and obesity, genuine.

00:41:20.800 --> 00:41:22.805 align:middle line:90%
It's not so much--

00:41:22.805 --> 00:41:24.180 align:middle line:84%
if you look at it
away from food.

00:41:24.180 --> 00:41:26.970 align:middle line:84%
If you just look at it
from a science perspective

00:41:26.970 --> 00:41:31.530 align:middle line:84%
on just TVs, and the size--
it's my theory-- the size of TVs

00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:33.330 align:middle line:90%
and the size of human beings.

00:41:33.330 --> 00:41:34.650 align:middle line:90%
Let's go back in time.

00:41:34.650 --> 00:41:37.680 align:middle line:84%
So listen, when there
were one channel, two,

00:41:37.680 --> 00:41:40.770 align:middle line:84%
three different TV channels,
and a television screen

00:41:40.770 --> 00:41:45.270 align:middle line:84%
was this big, then human
beings were so big.

00:41:45.270 --> 00:41:48.300 align:middle line:84%
And then what happened was,
we had four or five channels,

00:41:48.300 --> 00:41:50.220 align:middle line:90%
then we went to 10 channels.

00:41:50.220 --> 00:41:51.840 align:middle line:84%
And then the TV's
got slightly larger.

00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:55.230 align:middle line:84%
We started seeing things
like 22-inch screens.

00:41:55.230 --> 00:41:57.240 align:middle line:90%
And humans got bigger.

00:41:57.240 --> 00:41:59.160 align:middle line:84%
